On March 15th, the Jura canton in Switzerland announced conditions for the operation of essential businesses, which come into effect March 16th:

Essential and food businesses that also sell non-essential items may remain open granted that they solely sell essential items to customers;

Essential and food businesses may open from 6 am to 8 pm (except for individual establishments that were granted exceptions);

Both customers and business owners and their employees must adhere by the sanitary precautions dictated by the Federal Office of Public Health, especially in terms of social distancing (through markings on the floor for instance);

People responsible for businesses and establishments that remain open must clearly display, the sanitary measures for individual and collective protection recommended by the Federal Office of Public Health.

